Here’s an example of a basic React component in the style promoted by DevSheets.io, using modern practices like hooks and TypeScript:

tsx
import { useState } from 'react';

export default function Counter() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

  return (
    <div className="p-4 border rounded-lg">
      <h2 className="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Counter Example</h2>
      <p className="mb-2">Count: {count}</p>
      <button
        className="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-500 text-white rounded"
        onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}
      >
        Increment
      </button>
    </div>
  );
}


This snippet follows modern React practices with TypeScript, clean styling using Tailwind CSS, and a focused component structure.
